gram<\/strong><\/li>\n<li><strong>PNP Entrepreneur Immigration<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n[\/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;1. Intra Company Transfer Canada&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column_text]<a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/intra-company-transfer-canada-ict-work-permit\/\"><strong>Intra Company Transfer Canada<\/strong><\/a> was designed for business owners who wish to <strong>expand their business from India to Canada<\/strong>. Candidates chosen under this program will be issued a <strong>temporary work permit<\/strong> to enter Canada and set up their business operations there. They will then get a chance to apply for permanent residence once they have operated their business in Canada for one year.<\/p>\n<p>It is one of the fastest Canadian Investment visas for Indian applicants. Look at our comprehensive guide to <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/intra-company-transfer-to-pr-canada\/\"><strong>Intra Company Transfer to PR Canada<\/strong><\/a> for more information.<\/p>\n<p><strong>You may also like: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/blog\/intra-company-transfer-from-india-to-canada\/\">Intra Company Transfer from India to Canada<\/a><\/strong>[\/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;2. C11 Entrepreneur Visa&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column_text]The <strong>C11 Entrepreneur Visa<\/strong> route is for entrepreneurs and self-employed individuals who intend to work in Canada and then apply for permanent resident status. This program issues such individuals a special <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/lmia-exempt-work-permit\/\"><strong>LMIA Exempt Work Permit<\/strong><\/a>. They can then work in Canada for a certain amount of time and apply for permanent resident status.[\/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;3. LMIA Work Permit Program&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column_text]The <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/lmia-work-permit\/\"><strong>LMIA Work Permit<\/strong><\/a> program isn\u2019t an investment-oriented immigration route. However, many Indians still use it to obtain permanent residence. This program is for people who have received a job offer from a Canadian employer who has received a positive LMIA. This means the employer can hire foreign workers after demonstrating they could not find Canadians to fill job vacancies.<\/p>\n<p>If you are issued a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/work-permit-canada\/\"><strong>work permit<\/strong><\/a> under this program, you can come to Canada and work for your employer. Once you have obtained two years of work experience, you can apply for permanent residence through the <a href=\"https:\/\/www.elaarimmigration.ca\/express-entry\/\"><strong>Express Entry<\/strong><\/a> system.[\/vc_column_text][vc_custom_heading text=&#8221;4. Provincial Nominee Programs for Business Owners &amp; Investors&#8221; use_theme_fonts=&#8221;yes&#8221;][vc_column_text]Each Canadian province, except Nunavut, offers immigration programs specifically for investors. Most of these cater to people who intend to start, purchase, and operate a business in the province. However, some programs also offer permanent residence to investors willing to make a sizable investment in the province. There are over a dozen provincial entrepreneur programs to choose from, so you should study each one carefully to determine which is right for you.<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/www.canada.ca\/en\/immigration-refugees-citizenship\/campaigns\/immigration-matters\/growing-canada-future\/business.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><strong>How Foreign Businesses Help Canada Grow?<\/strong><\/a>[\/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner equal_height=&#8221;yes&#8221; content_placement=&#8221;middle&#8221; column_margin=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_tablet=&#8221;default&#8221; column_direction_phone=&#8221;default&#8221; top_